title: National Defense Ministry
new-page: true
is-card: true
tags: govt_affairs, cabinet
on-arrival: military_policy_timer += 6; month_actions += 1
view-if: CHP_in_government = 1 and reichswehr_minister_party = "CHP" and military_policy_timer <= 0
card-image: img/portraits/Hasan_Esat_Isik.jpg
go-to: menu

= National Defense Ministry

@menu

The National Defense Ministry is the institution that enables cooperation between the civil government and the army high command. It is responsible for establishing the army budget managing the logistical needs of the armed forces. We can also use the ministry to ease down tensions with the army.

- @OYAK: Increase state support for the officers' investment fund, OYAK.
- @OYAKstrict: Open investigations on the spending of the OYAK funds.
- @budget: Increase the budget of the army.
- @budgetdecrease: Launch a campaign of inspections into the financial spending of the military.
- @modernize: Modernize army factories.
- @ASELSAN: Form ASELSAN.
- @root: No change to military policy.
- @easy_discard
- @cancel_advisor_action

@OYAK
subtitle: -1 budget.
choose-if: budget >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: We don't have enough budget!
on-arrival: coup_timer -= 1; budget -= 1

Despite the army officials claim that they represent a group of interest wholly devoted to the defense of the republic and not interested in petty material matters, they too constitute a player in the financial sector. State funding for their private investment fund ease the worries of the many and improve our relations with them.

@OYAKstrict
subtitle: It is a known fact that the army exerts influence over the financial and civil sectors through the OYAK funds.
choose-if: CGP_in_government == 0
unavailable_subtitle: Our coalition partner CGP is hostile to any attempts at limiting the influence of the army!
on-arrival: democracystatus += 2; coup_timer += 1

Our investigations reveal connections formed between the major industrial conglomerates and the army officers. While these intrusions into the affairs of the army will provide stability for our democracy by limiting the influence of the armed forces, we need to be careful about angering the army too much.

@budget
subtitle: -1 budget. We will have to decide how the increased budget will be spent.

- @local: Switch MKE deliveries towards internal production.
- @local2: Continue switching MKE deliveries towards internal production.
- @westernimport: Import military equipment directly from the West.
- @ee: Do not increase the military budget.

@local
subtitle: -1 budget. MKE, Mechanical and Chemical Industry Corporation, is our main supplier of army products. However we are currently dependent on Western imports.
view-if: MKE == 0
choose-if: budget >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: We don't have enough budget!
on-arrival: budget -= 1; MKE += 1; capitalist_chp += 3; petty_bourgeoisie += 2; forex_pressure -= 3; unemployment_modifier -= 0.4; growth_modifier += 0.4; industrial_production_index_modifier += 4

We begin shifting our equipment supplies from imports towards internal producers. Even though this is costly in the short term due to reestablishing our supply lines, the change improves our dependence on foreign currency and aid.

We will be able to retake this action without a budget decrease in the future.

@local2
subtitle: MKE, Mechanical and Chemical Industry Corporation, is our main supplier of army products. However we are currently dependent on Western imports.
view-if: MKE > 0
on-arrival: MKE += 1; capitalist_chp += 3; petty_bourgeoisie += 2; forex_pressure -= 2; unemployment_modifier -= 0.4; growth_modifier += 0.4; army_land_strength += 0.05; army_naval_strength += 0.05; army_aerial_strength += 0.05; industrial_production_index_modifier += 4

We continue improving our arms industry capabilities. Due to our sustained efforts our armed capabilities have begun improving, though to a lesser extent than would have been if we simply imported these equipments. 

@westernimport
subtitle: -1 budget. This has been our policy for long.
choose-if: budget >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: We don't have enough budget!
on-arrival: army_land_strength += 0.1; army_naval_strength += 0.1; army_aerial_strength += 0.1; budget -= 1

We import weaponry from Western countries to meet our equipment demands as usual.

@ee
go-to: menu

@budgetdecrease
on-arrival: coup_timer += 2; budget += 1
subtitle: +1 budget.
choose-if: CGP_in_government == 0
unavailable-subtitle: Our coalition partner CGP is hostile to any attempts at limiting the influence of the army!

We launch a campaign of inspections into the spendings of the army. The army views attempts at curbing excessive spending as an act of disrespect and many high ranking officials privately express their disapproval.

@modernize
subtitle: -1 budget.
choose-if: budget >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: We don't have enough budget!
on-arrival: budget -= 1; unemployment_modifier -= 0.5; army_land_strength += 0.1; army_naval_strength += 0.1; army_aerial_strength += 0.1; industrial_production_index_modifier += 4

@ASELSAN
subtitle: -1 budget. The TCG-Kocatepe incident has revealed the need for us to develop an independent arms industry, form a new Turkish arms company!
view-if: aselsann == 0 and year > 1974
choose-if: budget >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: We don't have enough budget!
on-arrival: coup_timer -= 1; aselsann += 1; army_land_strength += 0.1; army_naval_strength += 0.1; army_aerial_strength += 0.1; budget -= 1

The high command congratulate us for taking such a historic step.

